# Shared Lambda Layer Rules

`msg-lambda-layers/layers/shared/` is consumed by msg-guest, msg-guide, AND msg-marketplace. Changes here affect all three apps.

## Backward Compatibility — MUST

- NEVER rename, remove, or change the signature of existing methods in `event.py`, `decorators.py`, `data_loader.py`, entity classes, or factory classes.
- New methods and classes MAY be added freely.
- If a signature change is truly needed, confirm with the user first and document the migration path for all consuming apps.

## Key Modules

| Module | Contains |
|---|---|
| `event.py` | `Event` class — Supabase client, CacheWrapper, CRUD helpers, validation, identity, query building |
| `decorators.py` | `@klug()`, `@public_api()` — response standardization |
| `exceptions.py` | `BadJsonError`, `PathParameterError`, `QueryParameterError`, `ParameterError` |
| `helpers.py` | `normalize_name()`, `invalidate_guide_share_caches()` |
| `entities/` | `BaseEntity`/`BaseEntityFactory` and domain entities (all factories take `(supabase, cache=None)`) |
| `data_loader.py` | `CityDataLoader` — parallel queries via `ThreadPoolExecutor` |
| `mixpanel_util.py` | `track_event()`, `people_set()` |
| `experience_utils.py` | `generate_thumbnail_url()` |

## Testing Impact

Before merging changes, verify that endpoint tests in all three consuming apps still pass. A shared-layer change that breaks one app blocks all deployments.

## Third-Party Dependencies

Pinned in `layers/thirdparty/requirements.txt`. When adding or upgrading a dependency, verify compatibility with all three apps' Lambda runtimes.
